{"id":"1505.06479","submitter":"Terence C. Tao","authors":"Terence Tao","title":"Cancellation for the multilinear Hilbert transform","comments":"17 pages, no figures. An error pointed out to the author by Pavel\n  Zorin-Kranich has been corrected","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CA math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For any natural number $k$, consider the $k$-linear Hilbert transform $$ H_k(\nf_1,\\dots,f_k )(x) := \\operatorname{p.v.} \\int_{\\bf R} f_1(x+t) \\dots\nf_k(x+kt)\\ \\frac{dt}{t}$$ for test functions $f_1,\\dots,f_k: {\\bf R} \\to {\\bf\nC}$. It is conjectured that $H_k$ maps $L^{p_1}({\\bf R}) \\times \\dots \\times\nL^{p_k}({\\bf R}) \\to L^p({\\bf R})$ whenever $1 < p_1,\\dots,p_k,p < \\infty$ and\n$\\frac{1}{p} = \\frac{1}{p_1} + \\dots + \\frac{1}{p_k}$. This is proven for\n$k=1,2$, but remains open for larger $k$.\n  In this paper, we consider the truncated operators $$ H_{k,r,R}(\nf_1,\\dots,f_k )(x) := \\int_{r \\leq |t| \\leq R} f_1(x+t) \\dots f_k(x+kt)\\\n\\frac{dt}{t}$$ for $R > r > 0$. The above conjecture is equivalent to the\nuniform boundedness of $\\| H_{k,r,R} \\|_{L^{p_1}({\\bf R}) \\times \\dots \\times\nL^{p_k}({\\bf R}) \\to L^p({\\bf R})}$ in $r,R$, whereas the Minkowski and\nH\\\"older inequalities give the trivial upper bound of $2 \\log \\frac{R}{r}$ for\nthis quantity. By using the arithmetic regularity and counting lemmas of Green\nand the author, we improve the trivial upper bound on $\\| H_{k,r,R}\n\\|_{L^{p_1}({\\bf R}) \\times \\dots \\times L^{p_k}({\\bf R}) \\to L^p({\\bf R})}$\nslightly to $o( \\log \\frac{R}{r} )$ in the limit $\\frac{R}{r} \\to \\infty$ for\nany admissible choice of $k$ and $p_1,\\dots,p_k,p$. This establishes some\ncancellation in the $k$-linear Hilbert transform $H_k$, but not enough to\nestablish its boundedness in $L^p$ spaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 24 May 2015 20:49:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 May 2015 15:44:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 29 May 2015 18:20:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-01"}
